<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Deflower" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Deflower</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Deflour</orth> (rhyming to <cit><quote>Moor,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 191</bibl></cit>) to ravish: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 191</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 37</bibl>. Absolutely: <cit><quote>I must d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 348" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 348</bibl></cit>. Misapplied: <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.297" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 297</bibl>.*
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>